rabbitai resume` to resume automatic reviews.\n> - `@coderabbitai review` to trigger a single review.\n> \n> Use the checkboxes below for quick actions:\n> - [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"7f6cc2e2-2e4e-497a-8c31-c9e4573e93d1\"} --> ▶️ Resume reviews\n> - [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"e9bb8d72-00e8-4f67-9cb2-caf3b22574fe\"} --> 🔍 Trigger review\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: review paused by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nAdds cross-platform build/distribution scripts and Electron Builder changes; introduces build hooks and Windows node-pty patching; improves platform-aware path/agent resolution, terminal and font handling, per-window UI zoom persistence and IPC, and small renderer/main process UX adjustments.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Build & Distribution** <br> `package.json`, `README.md`|Reworked npm scripts (dev now runs `scripts/dev.js`, added `cross-env`, new `dist:windows`/`dist:linux`/`build:icon`), updated electron-builder config (asarUnpack, extraResources, beforeBuild hook, Windows icon/NSIS/portable artifact naming).|\n|**Build hooks & Windows tooling** <br> `scripts/before-build.js`, `scripts/patch-node-pty-win.js`, `scripts/create-ico.js`|Added before-build hook that applies `node-pty` Windows patches and generates cpu-features `buildcheck.gypi`; new patcher modifies winpty/binding gyps and writes GenVersion.h; ICO generator composes `resources/icon.ico` from PNG sizes.|\n|**Native rebuild / postinstall** <br> `package.json` (scripts)|Changed `rebuild`/`postinstall` to sequentially run `electron-rebuild -o better-sqlite3 -o node-pty`, run Windows patcher in postinstall, pinned `node-pty` to `1.1.0`, added `cross-env`, removed an optional dep.|\n|**Agent/path resolution & exec helpers** <br> `src/main/agent-paths.ts`, `src/main/ipc/agents.ts`|Platform-aware PATH resolution and fallback candidates; exported `whichSync`; switch from shell `exec` to `execFile`-style probing and literal-arg version checks; resolve/promote spawnable executables (prefer `.exe` on Windows) and revalidate cached agent paths.|\n|**Terminal / PTY & renderer terminal** <br> `src/main/ipc/terminal.ts`, `src/renderer/src/components/TerminalTile.tsx`|Windows: skip node-pty spawn-helper discovery, expand allowlist to include `powershell`/`pwsh`/`cmd`, treat tmux as unavailable; renderer: async font registration, Nerd Font fallback stack, Unicode11 + optional WebGL addons, live fontSize updates, safer init/teardown.|\n|**Main process & window UI** <br> `src/main/index.ts`, `src/main/windowAppearance.ts`, `src/main/chrome-sync/keychain.ts`|OS-specific icon selection (`.ico` on Windows), apply saved per-window zoom on load, adjust titleBar/frame/transparency per-OS, and guard Chrome keychain access to macOS only.|\n|**UI zoom IPC & persistence** <br> `src/main/ipc/ui.ts`, `src/preload/index.ts`, `src/renderer/src/env.d.ts`|New `ui-state.json` persistence and IPC (`ui:getZoomLevel` / `ui:setZoomLevel`), exports `getSavedZoomLevel()` and `registerUIIPC()`; preload exposes `platform` and `zoom` bridge; renderer types updated.|\n|**Renderer UX / behavior tweaks** <br> `src/renderer/src/App.tsx`, `src/renderer/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/renderer/src/components/MCPPanel.tsx`, `src/renderer/src/hooks/useMCPServers.ts`|Zoom keyboard now adjusts Electron UI zoom (and canvas reset), sidebar expand can trigger workspace switch, unified home dir resolution via `__HOME__`/`HOME`/`USERPROFILE`, MCP config path adjustments.|\n|**Fonts & shared defaults** <br> `src/shared/types.ts`|Monospace fallback stack reordered to prefer `\"FiraCode Nerd Font Mono\"` first to improve terminal glyph coverage.|\n|**FS / misc utilities** <br> `src/main/ipc/fs.ts`, `bin/codesurfd.mjs`|Removed noisy home-path warning, clarified ENOENT handling in `fs:stat`, unified HOME/USERPROFILE/homedir fallback in CLI session index path.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Renderer\n    participant Preload\n    participant Main\n    participant FS\n\n    Renderer->>Preload: window.electron.zoom.setLevel(level)\n    Preload->>Main: ipcRenderer.invoke('ui:setZoomLevel', level)\n    Main->>FS: write merged ui-state.json (persist zoomLevel)\n    FS-->>Main: write complete\n    Main->>Renderer: win.webContents.setZoomLevel(level)\n    Main-->>Preload: resolve invoke promise\n    Preload-->>Renderer: promise resolves\n```\n\n## Estimated code review effort\n\n🎯 4 (Complex) | ⏱️ ~60 minutes\n\n## Possibly related PRs\n\n- jasonkneen/codesurf#1 — overlaps native module rebuild and postinstall/before-build changes.\n\n## Poem\n\n> 🐇 I hopped through scripts and patched a pty,  \n> icons stacked tidy so Windows can see.  \n> Nerd fonts lined up, terminals hum okay,  \n> zooms tucked in files to remember the day.  \n> A rabbit taps Enter — cross-platform hooray!\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 2 | ❌ 1</summary>\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 warning)\n\n|     Check name     | Status     | Explanation                                                                           | Resolution                                                                         |\n| :----------------: | :--------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :--------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Docstring Coverage | ⚠️ Warning | Docstring coverage is 35.71% which is insufficient. The required threshold is 80.00%. | Write docstrings for the functions missing them to satisfy the coverage threshold. |\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (2 passed)</summary>\n\n|     Check name    | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                      